	"message": "The suggestion to visit Istanbul, while well-intentioned as a means to offer comfort and change, might be perceived as insensitive because it could imply that the grieving process could be eased simply by traveling. The complexity and individuality of grief, especially soon after a loss, makes it generally more appropriate to focus on emotional support rather than suggesting significant activities or changes."
}
